cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.SE, cs.AR, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on reducing power consumption in a server cluster through DVFS control algorithms. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper proposes a hybrid DVFS control system that combines an empirical performance model and a feedback controller for adaption. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper proposes a request tracing approach to monitor the performance data of a multi-tier service. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is relevant as the paper discusses DVFS (Dynamic voltage and frequency scaling) control algorithms, which are related to hardware architecture. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is relevant as the paper aims to improve system performance while reducing power consumption.
